[Loveland is about 17 km south of Fort Collins in north central Colorado. A
fatal case of HPS occurred last year just outside Loveland in a rural area
but the present case, which had onset more than a month ago, likely was
acquired in Arizona. The statement that "10%-15% of the mouse population
carries the virus" is a misquote or misstatement. John Pape knows quite
well that antibody prevalence (taken to indicate the presence of virus in
persistently infected rodents) can range from 0 to 40% or more, depending
on location and year. No serosurveys have been done in Larimer County,
where Loveland and Fort Collins are located, so the antibody prevalence
there is unknown. In addition, "mice" is understood (not stated) to mean
deer mice, _Peromyscus maniculatus_. - Mod.CHC
...........................chc/es
